  • Method Details

    • getTag

      ProfilerTag getTag()
      Returns:
      Identifier of the frame; doesn't have to be unique

    • getOffset

      int getOffset()
      Returns:
      Time in millis from when the stack started to when this frame was pushed on to the stack

    • getElapsedTime

      int getElapsedTime()
      Returns:
      Amount of time in millis that the frame was open, difference between pop time and push time, this includes all the elapsed time of children; -1 if the frame is still on the stack ("open")

    • getFrameTime

      int getFrameTime()
      Returns:
      Amount of time spent in this frame, does not include the elapsed time of children; ; -1 if the frame is still on the stack ("open")

    • getChildrenElapsedTime

      int getChildrenElapsedTime()
      Returns:
      Elapsed time in millis spent in children of this frame

    • getNumChildren

      int getNumChildren()
      Returns:
      Number of children for this frame.

    • getChildren

      List<ProfilerFrame> getChildren()
      Returns:
      The children of this frame

    • flatten

      default Stream<ProfilerFrame> flatten()
      This will return this and all its children recursively. This effectively walks the tree, note that getParent() will return the parent inside of the stream.
      Returns:
      Stream of ProfilerFrames

    • getPropertiesAndCounters

      Map<String,Object> getPropertiesAndCounters()
      Returns:
      A map of all the properties and counters, hashed by name

    • incrementCounter

      int incrementCounter(String name)
      Increments the value of a counter by one. If the counter doesn't exist a new counter is created w/ a value of one.
      Parameters:
      name - Name of counter

    • setCounterValue

      void setCounterValue(String name, int value)
      Set the value of a counter
      Parameters:

      value - Value of the counter

    • hasCounter

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      True if the counter exists; false otherwise

    • getCounterValue

      int getCounterValue(String name)
      Get the value of a specific counter
      Parameters:
      name - Name of the counter
      Returns:
      Value of the counter or 0 if the counter doesn't exist

    • getParent

      ProfilerFrame getParent()

      boolean isClosed()
